<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-10685] Index transaction dealing with cleanup doesn&apos;t notify indexes of partition deletion</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10685</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;SecondaryIndexManager.CleanupGCTransaction&lt;/tt&gt; doesn&apos;t notify registered indexers of the partition level deletion on commit. Indexers &lt;b&gt;are&lt;/b&gt; notified of each individual row removal caused by the partition delete, but also informing them of the top level delete would enable them to make potential optimizations during cleanup. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12911939">CASSANDRA-10685</key>
            <summary>Index transaction dealing with cleanup doesn&apos;t notify indexes of partition deletion</summary>
