                            <comment id="14999129" author="beobal" created="Tue, 10 Nov 2015 19:05:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is an oversight that was missed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-9459&quot; title=&quot;SecondaryIndex API redesign&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-9459&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-9459&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;CleanupGCTransaction::onPartitionDeletion&lt;/tt&gt; is being called by &lt;tt&gt;SIM::deletePartition&lt;/tt&gt;, it just then doesn&apos;t do anything with the supplied &lt;tt&gt;DeletionTime&lt;/tt&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is however, a complication in that the partition passed to &lt;tt&gt;SIM::deletePartition&lt;/tt&gt; isn&apos;t technically deleted by a cleanup (it&apos;s just not included in the rewritten sstables), so we have to fabricate a &lt;tt&gt;DeletionTime&lt;/tt&gt; to pass on to the &lt;tt&gt;Indexers&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

